# 🧠 Interview‑Ready Answer (30 seconds)

> Service Workers intercept all network requests, including POST requests, but they do not cache POST requests by default. Caching POST requests is unsafe because they mutate data. The recommended approach is to allow POST, PUT, and DELETE requests to pass directly to the network, while caching only GET requests. POST handling is only implemented in Service Workers when using advanced features like background sync for offline submission scenarios.

